Under optimal experimental conditions, the absorbance of Au-cys upon incubation with different concentrations of profenofos was investigated (Fig. 2
                        ). As the concentration of profenofos increased, the color of the system changed from red to purple, and finally to blue (Fig. 2A). However, the absorbance decreased at 520 nm, while the decrease was more gradual at higher wavelengths (Fig. 2B). When the concentration of profenofos was higher than 1.4 mg L−1, the absorbance at higher wavelengths was almost unchanged or decreased. When the concentration of profenofos was in the range of 0.2–1.2 mg L−1, there was a linear relationship in the difference in absorbance between 520 nm and 800 nm (A520-A800) (Fig. 2C). The linear regression equation was A520-A800 = -0.1240 C
                        profenofos + 0.2907 (R2 = 0.993). The LOD is calculated as 21.7 μg L−1 at a signal to noise ratio of 3. The colorimetric sensor in the UV–vis mode was sensitive for the rapid detection of profenofos within 7 min.
